Introduction

PURPLE KISS (sometimes known as Purki), also stylized as PURPLE K!SS, is a six-member South Korean girl group formed by RBW Entertainment. The group debuted on March 15, 2021, with the mini album “INTO VIOLET”, with the title track “Ponzona”.

Before their official debut, they released two singles: “My Heart Skip a Beat” on November 26, 2020, and “Can We Talk Again” on February 3, 2021. Two of the members, Jieun and Goeun also participated in Produce 48, the third season of the Produce series, an Mnet’s idol survival show.

On November 18, 2022, RBW released a statement revealing that Jieun would be leaving PURPLE KISS due to poor physical conditions and anxiety symptoms.
